# Git Commit Message Template
# 
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# 
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation changes
#   style    - Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
#   refactor - Code refactoring
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks
#   perf     - Performance improvements
#   ci       - CI/CD changes
#   build    - Build system changes
# 
# Scopes (examples):
#   docs     - Documentation
#   sql      - SQL examples/queries
#   docker   - Docker configuration
#   scripts  - Scripts and automation
#   config   - Configuration files
#   ui       - User interface
#   api      - API changes
#   db       - Database changes
# 
# Rules:
# - Keep subject line under 50 characters
# - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
# - Don't end with period
# - Be specific and concise
# 
# Examples:
#   feat(sql): add recursive CTE cheatsheet
#   fix(docs): correct typo in learning path
#   docs(sql): improve example documentation
#   refactor(scripts): simplify docker setup
#   test(sql): add validation for CTE examples
# 
# Delete all lines starting with # to commit

<type>(<scope>): <subject>

# Optional: Add detailed description below (separated by blank line)
# 
# - What was changed and why
# - Any breaking changes
# - Related issues or tickets
# 
# Keep each line under 72 characters 